1 WHEREAS, Mr. Durham was a faithful man and longtime member of East Jena
2 Baptist Church; his life was grounded in his strong and steady faith, and he was known as
3 a devoted follower of Christ; he was also a member of the Michael Dempsey Lodge, where
4 he built numerous friendships and remained actively involved in the community; and
5 WHEREAS, Mr. Durham was most notably a loving husband, father, grandfather,
6 and great-grandfather; he cherished his family and found immense joy in the company of his
7 great-grandchildren; and
8 WHEREAS, Clarence Durham is survived by his brother, Dallie "D.L." Durham;
9 sons, Gerald Durham (Kris), Robert Durham (Janie), and Brian Durham (Sheila);
10 grandchildren, Stephen Durham, Robbie Durham (Danna), Katherine Smith (Caleb), Jeffrey
11 Durham (Courtney), Hope Worthan (Jacob), Daisy Hooter (Jake), Faith Durham, Cyera
12 Durham, and Donnie Durham; sixteen great-grandchildren; and numerous extended relatives
13 and friends; he will be deeply missed, but the legacy of his love and service to his family,
14 friends, community, and nation shall live on in the hearts and minds of those who were
15 privileged to have known and loved him.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
17 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Clarence
18 Durham, the last living LaSalle Parish World War II veteran; does hereby offer enduring
19 appreciation and respect for Mr. Durham's outstanding military service; and does hereby
20 extend sincere wishes that his family, friends, and loved ones find comfort in their shared
21 memories of his inspiring life.
